This suite tests basic invocations of all functions.

The goal to test if functions work on basic, hello-world level inputs, as a
overall runtime coverage metric, as opposed to detailed unit tests.

The math and complex subsuites are generated using misc/genbasic.c and verify
that the mathematical results are bit perfect and that special cases are
handled with correct error handling. Implementations will fail if they do not
have full precision with correct rounding.
